## Falsifier preregister (15 across 5 measurable claims)

### Genus distinction (F-NB-1)
- **F-NB-1-genus** = actuator-state-cycle-presence: NANOBOT must exhibit ≥4 distinct mechanical states (S0..S3) with directed transitions and net `work_per_cycle ≥10 kT`. Falsified if a candidate primitive admits only static binding (VIROCAPSID-class) or single-step catalysis (RIBOZYME-class) or weave/composition (WEAVE-class) without a closed cycle. Audit: F-NB-4 witness `state_visit_counts` non-zero on all 4 states + `productive_cycles ≥ 0.5 × n_cycles_completed/2`. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via `_python_bridge/module/sister_genus_audit.py` direct-read; cycle-24 MVP shows 4 states visited, productive_cycles=2168 ≥ threshold 754.5 (= 0.5 × 3018 / 2). Witness `raw_77_nanobot_subclause_direct_read_v2`.
- **F-NB-1-b** = Brownian-margin-numerical: NANOBOT genus distinct from passive Brownian ratchet — work output must exceed kT noise floor by margin ≥10 kT in simulation, not merely thermodynamic-feasible. Falsified if Langevin sim shows `work_per_cycle_kT < 10` under 310K. Cross-checks F-NB-3-floor. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via same audit (50.0 kT >> 10 kT threshold; transitive with F-NB-3-floor PASS).
- **F-NB-1-c** = sister-axis-collision: NANOBOT primitive must not collapse onto WEAVE (composition) / RIBOZYME (catalysis) / VIROCAPSID (static cage) axes. Falsified if N-R2 boundary audit (F-NB-5) finds >50% functional overlap with any sister verb. Witness: F-NB-5 audit `collision_overlap_ratio < 0.5`. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** Quantitative collision-overlap measurement protocol implemented: `_python_bridge/module/nanobot_n_r2_boundary_audit.py` (stdlib only) + witness schema `nanobot/spec/n_r2_boundary_audit_v1.schema.json` (raw_77_nanobot_n_r2_boundary_audit_v1). Script extracts L0-L6 primitives from raw_77_nanobot_actuation_v1 and computes Jaccard collision_overlap_ratio = |L0-L6 ∩ L7-L9| / |L0-L6 ∪ L7-L9| against canonical handoff JSON; PASS when ratio < 0.5. Initial run 2026-05-06 08:00Z: status=CANONICAL_PENDING, ratio=null. **Closure run 2026-05-06 09:05Z** (canonical JSON landed at `~/core/canon/domains/life/therapeutic-nanobot/handoff/2026-05-28_hexa-nanobot-therapeutic-nanobot-boundary.json` v1.0.0-stub DECLARED): collision_overlap_ratio=**0.0** (intersection empty across n=7 L0-L6 vs n=7 L7-L9 disjoint primitive labels) → status=PASS. F-NB-1-c PASS gate `< 0.5` satisfied with full disjointness. Stub-handoff caveat: PASS certifies architectural-axis non-collision only (definitional disjointness via canonical primitive label choice); wet-lab integration + IP/contract review deferred to cycle 30+ per canonical raw_91 C3 disclosure.

