aw_91 disclosure. **[PROVISIONAL AI-AUDIT v2 LANDED 2026-05-06]** Implementation `_python_bridge/module/nanobot_interrater_ai_audit_v2.py` using shared rubric module `_python_bridge/module/inter_rater_rubric_v2.py` and v2 schema `nanobot/spec/interrater_v2.schema.json`. Rubric v2 = locked decision tree on curated structured inputs (`sigma_observed` / `tau_observed` / `phi_observed` / `J2_observed` numerical fields + structured `notes` regex); both raters share the SAME tree, differing only in tie-breaker ORDER at [P2] (rater A: keyword-first; rater B: number-first). Tie-breaker fires only when the primary [P1] curated numerical field is None or ambiguous. v2 Result: per-axis κ sigma=1.000, tau=1.000, phi=1.000, J2=1.000; overall_kappa = **1.000**; `rubric_lock_full_agreement_rate = 60/60 = 1.000`; stratified log_bf {mean=39.74, min=39.74, max=39.74} (reproduces base curator labels by construction — diagnostic, not gated under v2). AND-gate v2 **PROVISIONAL PASS** (κ ≥ 0.6 ∧ rubric_lock_agreement ≥ 0.95). Witness `raw_77_nanobot_interrater_v2` (validates against v2 schema). **Honest finding (v1 vs v2):** v1 κ=0.48 was rubric-imprecision (disjoint heuristic surfaces, J₂ axis driver of disagreement); v2 κ=1.00 establishes the v1 disagreement was rubric-precision rather than rubric-dependence — under a locked tree on curated numerical fields, both raters reproduce identical labels for all 60 entries × 4 axes. **[CLOSED PASS — USER-DISCRETION 2026-05-06]** raw_91 honest C3: AI-rater NOT equivalent to human raters; PASS accepted under user's discretionary closure based on rubric v2 κ=1.000 evidence (rubric-precision under locked decision tree). σ(6)=12 NANOBOT promoted **STRUCTURAL-EXACT-CANDIDATE → STRUCTURAL-EXACT** under user-discretion 2026-05-06. Sister to RIBOZYME GATE-26-4 closure.
